The <strong><code>PositionOptions</code></strong> interface describes an object containing option properties to pass as a parameter of <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/API/Geolocation/getCurrentPosition" title="The Geolocation.getCurrentPosition() method is used to get the current position of the device."><code>Geolocation.getCurrentPosition()</code></a> and <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/API/Geolocation/watchPosition" title="The Geolocation method watchPosition() method is used to register a handler function that will be called automatically each time the position of the device changes. You can also, optionally, specify an error handling callback function."><code>Geolocation.watchPosition()</code></a>.